.SH NAME
MediaTrackSettings.cursor \- MediaTrackSettings: cursor property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]MediaTrackSettings\f[R] dictionary\[cq]s
\f[B]\f[CB]cursor\f[B]\f[R] property indicates whether or not the cursor
should be captured as part of the video track included in the
\f[CR]MediaStream\f[R] returned by \f[CR]getDisplayMedia()\f[R].
.SH VALUE
The value of \f[CR]cursor\f[R] comes from the
\f[CR]CursorCaptureConstraint\f[R] enumerated string type, and may have
one of the following values:
.TP
\f[B]always\f[R]
The mouse should always be visible in the video content of the
\f[CR]MediaStream\f[R], unless the mouse has moved outside the area of
the content.
.TP
\f[B]motion\f[R]
The mouse cursor should always be included in the video if it\[cq]s
moving, and for a short time after it stops moving.
.TP
\f[B]never\f[R]
The mouse cursor is never included in the shared video.
